definitions: To fill a container or space tightly with something.
To push or cram something into a space or container.
To fill the skin of a dead animal with material to restore its original appearance.
To fill food, such as poultry or vegetables, with a mixture before cooking.
To eat a large amount of food.
examples: She began to stuff clothes into her suitcase.
He stuffed the letter into his pocket.
The taxidermist will stuff the bird.
We're going to stuff the turkey for Thanksgiving.
I really stuffed myself at dinner.
